description:
Location: secretx-pkcs11/src/lib.rs:62 — pub fn from_uri lacks a `# Errors` rustdoc section.

clippy::missing_errors_doc (pedantic) flags this. Public Result-returning functions should document the error conditions in a rustdoc `# Errors` section.

Current state: the rustdoc above from_uri (lines 58-61) describes the happy path and notes "No session is opened until a trait method is called", but does not enumerate when from_uri returns Err.

Suggested addition:

    /// # Errors
    ///
    /// Returns [`SecretError::InvalidUri`] when:
    /// - the URI does not start with `secretx:pkcs11:`
    /// - the path does not match `<slot>/<label>` with non-empty parts
    /// - the slot component is not a non-negative integer
    /// - neither `?lib=...` nor the `PKCS11_LIB` env var is set
    ///
    /// Returns [`SecretError::Backend`] when:
    /// - the PKCS#11 library cannot be loaded (missing or non-conforming `.so`)
    /// - `C_Initialize` fails
    /// - `C_GetSlotList` fails
    /// - the requested slot index is out of range

This is the public entry point of the crate; it deserves the most attention in docs. Other public methods (sign, get, put, public_key_der, refresh, algorithm) inherit their doc contracts from the trait, so they don't need # Errors here, but from_uri does.
